<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 3:21PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of western Sherman and
northeastern Dallam Counties through 400 PM CDT...
At 321 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northwest of Conlen, or 13 miles west of Stratford, moving east
at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Stratford and Conlen.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
